##DESCRIPTION
##  Interval of convergence for power series
##ENDDESCRIPTION

##KEYWORDS('Power Series')

DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

# No partial credit on this problem, so we say:
install_problem_grader(~~&std_problem_grader);


TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;

$a = random(2,10,1);
$b = random(1,11,1);
$c = random(2,11,1);
$d = 3*$c+2 ;

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

Find  the interval of convergence for the given  power series.
\[  \sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{n^{$c}(x + $b)^n}{($a^n)(n^{\frac{$d}{3}})} \]
The series is convergent:  
$BR
from \( x \) = \{ ans_rule(5)\}, left end included (enter Y or N): \{ ans_rule(2) \} $BR
to   \( x \) = \{ ans_rule(5) \}, right end included (enter Y or N): \{ ans_rule(2) \}

EOT

$ans1 = -$a - $b ;
$ans2 = "Y" ;
$ans3 = -$b  + $a ;
$ans4 = "N";

ANS(num_cmp($ans1));
ANS(str_cmp($ans2));
ANS(num_cmp($ans3));
ANS(str_cmp($ans4));

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
